  "texts": [
    "To illustrate this point, we now turn to a thought experiment involving Bertrand competition.",
    "Consider a simplified market with two airlines, each using agentic AI for dynamic pricing, and a large pool of prospective travelers-each likewise represented by its own agentic AI purchasing agent.",
    "In a traditional Bertrand competition with human buyers, even a small price difference would ordinarily cause nearly all demand to flow to the less expensive airline.",
    "By contrast, in a two-sided algorithmic market, both sellers (airlines) and buyers (travelers' purchasing agents) make decisions autonomously and strategically, potentially producing different outcomes.",
    "For instance, suppose both airlines initially charge a relatively high (collusive) fare."
  ],
